{"sequence":97,"timestamp":"2026-04-18T05:35:13.305032588Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-2f43664e","body":"finding_summary: The iterative stability check fingerprints the whole worktree instead of just source edits. In `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:6256-6448`, both the git and non-git paths treat any tracked/generated file churn as `diff_changed=true`; in this repository `result:1` is a tracked symlink, so a normal `nix build` can change the fingerprint even when the implementer made no source edits. That means `iterative_minimal` can keep burning rounds until `max_rounds` instead of exiting as stable.\naffected_files: [src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:6256-6448, result:1]\nremediation_hint: Exclude verification/build artifacts from the fingerprint (at minimum `result` and non-source directories like `target/`), or compute stability from a filtered source-file status set rather than the raw worktree diff.","dedup_key":"cc3e0f0f5741e72b7298bacbdbd3abb1c719964a39729dab00b96999a1e0e935","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260418021911","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":98,"timestamp":"2026-04-18T05:35:13.314565258Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-020cdd6b","body":"`persist_invocation_parsed_payload` is called unconditionally inside `invoke_stage_on_backend` (src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs, after every successful `agent_service.invoke(...)`), so every flow — Standard, Minimal, DocsChange, CiImprovement, QuickDev — now writes `runtime/backend/<invocation_id>.parsed.json` on every stage invocation. The iterative-minimal work was supposed to be ADDITIVE, but this introduces a new side effect (new file writes, new inode churn, potentially large JSON blobs persisted for stages that never read them back) for every existing flow. It also uses plain `fs::write` instead of `FileSystem::write_atomic`, which is the convention in this codebase for any file the engine may reread. Gate the call on `invocation_suffix.is_some()` (i.e., only for iterative iterations that need to recover the parsed payload on resume), and switch the write to `FileSystem::write_atomic` so a crash mid-write can't leave a truncated file that `recover_iterative_iteration_result` will later try to parse. Add a regression test that runs a `minimal` flow and asserts `runtime/backend/` contains no `*.parsed.json` artifacts for non-iterative stages.","dedup_key":"e6db806a80a48c4700458217ca0e15936402713d71b907ac3125f9524b758362","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-7-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260418021911","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
